OL,3,CMum accused of murdering son, three,
OL,4,Cdenies he was an 'inconvenience'
OL,6,FThe defendant, who is a follower of
OL,7,Fthe Black Hebrew Israelites religion,
OL,8,Fhas told the jury at Newcastle Crown
OL,9,FCourt that prior to his death, she hit
OL,10,Fhim with a bamboo garden cane as a
OL,11,F"correction" for playing with his food.
OL,13,FShe explained she was following a
OL,14,FYouTube video about the religion which
OL,15,Ftalked about the Bible encouraging the
OL,16,Fuse of the rod for discipline.
OL,18,FBut she has denied violently shaking
OL,19,Fhim, causing a fatal brain injury,
OL,20,Fclaiming he collapsed while eating.
